-- EUROPE RESEARCH ROUNDUP-Aveva, Erste Group, RWE 
-- 
-- Fri Jul 04, 2014 01:15AM EDT
-- None



July 4 (Reuters) - Securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several European companies, including Alpha Bank, Hiscox and Mobotix, on Friday.

HIGHLIGHTS * Alpha Bank <ACBr.AT>: Renaissance Capital raises to hold from sell rating  * Hiscox <HSX.L>: Berenberg raises to hold from sell rating * Mobotix <MBQGn.DE>: DZ Bank cuts to sell from buy ratingFollowing is a summary of research actions on European companies reported by Reuters on Friday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order.  * Alpha Bank <ACBr.AT>: Renaissance Capital raises to hold from sell rating  * Aveva Group <AVV.L>: SocGen starts with a buy rating; price target 2,650p * Erste Group <ERST.VI>: Barclays cuts to underweight from equal weight  * Erste Group <ERST.VI>: Barclays cuts target price to 21.40 euros from 28 euros * Hiscox <HSX.L>: Berenberg raises to hold from sell rating * Hiscox <HSX.L>: Berenberg raises target price to 706p from 626p  * Mobotix <MBQGn.DE>: DZ Bank cuts to sell from buy; target price to 8.50 eur from 16 eur  * National Bank Of Greece <NBGr.AT>: Renaissance Capital raises to buy from sell  * Piraeus Bank <BOPr.AT>: Renaissance Capital raises target price to 1.39 euros from 1.28